<br>
If it's an NTFS partition run the XP installer and choose a Repair installation.  Hope you have a Rescue Disk made.  If you don't you can still repair but it won't be as clean.<br>
<br>
Once back in XP use the Disk Manager to make use of that 5GB floating - might want to recoup it into another partition.<br>
<br>
And yes - Linux has a problem if it's /boot section is above 1,024 cylinders.  Doesn't matter where you put /root, /home and such at but always put /boot low on the drive (before the 4GB point).<br>
<br>
Hope this helps.<br>
